<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xeo_Solro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hail Clerics of Norrath,<P>I am slowly approaching level 19 and I have my eye on the Celestrial Remedy.  I have a couple questions though.  Is this spell effective at with the large mana cost?  Does any kind of focus items effect it (healing, buff length, ...)?  When I get 24 and gheal I will no longer use this spell correct?<P>Here is the link for the spell on Lucy. <A HREF="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2502&source=Live" TARGET=_blank>http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2502&source=Live</A> <P>Thank you <BR>Xeo, Cleric of Solusek Ro<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">blueninja</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Focus items I am not sure of so I will leave that for someone else.<P>However this spell isn't all that bad even though it isn't that efficient with mana. Because it heals over time there is much less aggro induced from it than with the ordinary kind of heals. Also the target doesn't need to be down as many points as it heals, you can still get the full effect of it if the target is taking damage while the spell is working. If you cast greater heal then your tank must be down the full 300 odd points that gh heals otherwise you're wasting mana. Aggro is the biggest advantage though, IMO.<P>That said, I hardly ever used that spell. Not sure why, I use the level 44 version all the time and if I leveled a new cleric through those levels today I proably would use it  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> ..<P>------------------<BR>Picklesworth,<BR>level 51 high elf cleric on Fennin ro server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">clericx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I love the Celestial line of healing spells. They are very low agro and save me from a whooping more than once. I think many low level cleric will love this spell.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xeo_Solro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmm...does anyone know then if any focus items will help its healing power?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Badany</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I think the only focus effect that will work on Celestial spells is the Spell Casting Haste one.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28272" TARGET=_blank>Badany Greatheal</A><BR>Templar of the Prime Healer Rodcet Nife<BR>Zebuxoruk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">piikaa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I cast Celestial Heal / Complete Heal as my two primary heals in a regular exp group.  I'll use Complete when I want to let the warrior Berzerk, or if I am conserving mana.  I'l use celestial when I want to top him off or not draw agro.<P>EVERY TIME I cast Celestial Heal, my Black Alloy Medallion shimmers...<P>Piikaa Fishweed<BR>46th Drunken Dwarven Battlecleric of Brell<BR>Proud offficer of the Twilight Order - Bertox</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jaxga_Ironash</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Use Celestial Remedy at 19, it will be your main tank-healing spell until you get to level 24. The reason is because you can cast it early, sit down and med, and have the mana back by the time your tank needs another. Patch heal with Healing when it's really rough.<P>At level 24, you may still use it at the start of fights, simply because you can cast it on your tank as that nasty 5-pull comes in and forget about him for awhile to focus on your enchanter who's probably in need of some heals, roots, stuns, etc.<P>At least, that's how I used it.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corish-MT</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Great spell, a bit mana hoggish.<P>At 19, you'll probably find it useful to cast once per fight (basically at the start so the tank has time to build up aggro for you to switch to your more efficient heals).  More then that, and you'll be oom sooner.  My rule of thumb was I could cast it an additional time per fight for every additional spell circle above 19 without running low on mana.  Around level 39 or so, you'll really start pining for your level 44 CelHeal spell.<P>And for low aggro heals, don't forget to try using your braver-valor line of buffs as fairly efficient heals.<P>------------------<BR>Corish, 52 Cleric of Morell-Thule</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Feias</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok I don't understand the thought of cast it, sit and med and you will have the mana back before you cast it again....<P>The cast time is longer than that of GHeal and it heals less.  So....<P>Cast GHeal sit and med<BR>or<BR>Cast Celestial Remedy sit and med<BR>and<BR>You will have healed (going to be charitable to CR) the same amount of damage and had the same amount of med time with either.<P>The only difference is that one is still working after you cast and begin medding.  There is no difference in how fast you can med your mana back or in needing to throw a heal sooner.<P>The only bonus this spell has because it costs more mana for less healing, takes longer to cast, and isn't instant is that it incurs less agro.<P>Agro is the only bonus to this spell.  And honestly at level 19 I never had to worry about it.<p>[This message has been edited by Feias (edited 06-13-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ambul Ants</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't realy get this spell either, the places you hunt at the level you get this just don't warrent avoiding agro.<P>If anything it's a practice spell.  Avoiding agro when the mobs hit for 15 is just not as important as getting your defence skills up,  which you will need later for sure.<P>I was well past this spell when it came out so I may be missing something here. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serenya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Where I found this spell moderately useful was with damage shields, it tends to heal in pace with the damage taken.  I know 'take the shield down' -- well, this is my normal course of events.  Cast nullify magic -- shield still up cause I got the SK's ensnaring darkness; wait for recycyle and cast again -- oops, this time I got the mana tap the chanter dropped on it; wait and cast.  Got it!  Followed immediately by the mob dropping dead. ;p  I still try, but the refresh time is so long I usually end up better off if I just wait till one of my tanks needs a heal.  /sigh</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jaxga_Ironash</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Celestial Remedy is level 19.<P>Greater Heal is level 24.<P>At level 20 (fighting in the sarnak fort in ill omen), competing with level 24 druids/shaman that also have Healing, it's nice to have a 300 point, low aggro heal to show em who the real healers are.<P>Also, keep in mind that at level 20 your tank is going to have about 900 hps or so with your buffs.. so healing a 20 warrior for 1/3 of his health is a slightly bigger deal.<P>At level 24, you may still have this heal up, say you G-Heal your tank (heals 2 bubbles of health) and he's still down a bubble.. drop a CR on him and sit down and med (instead of waiting for the tank to take damage).<P>Your mileage may vary, like any other spell you should play with it until you have a feel for what it does.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Texbless</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I use this spell at the time at that lvl.<BR>The agro manament was key because it kept gouls from jumping on me.<P>Texbless 33 cleric sullon zek.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bombudil</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cel Rem is in most cases not that useful, however, there are 2 clear-cut cases where it is superior to the other healings in your arsenal:<P>1) Three mobs arrive together with puller. Chanter is already starting to panick. ---> Throw chanter a Cel Heal, and concentrate on the main tank (keep eye on chanter health of course). Chanter can now go through the mobs mezzing relatively safer that without the Cel Rem.<P>2) If you are doing dungeon zones. Sitting in LOIO doing standard pulls, you are fine. Even getting aggro wont kill you unless you are naked.<BR>However, there are dungeons accessible to you soon where aggro will kill you. I lived in Sol A from 25 and up to 29, and during this time I used Cel Rem frequently. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok, let me try to explain good use of HoT's.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Full mana is WASTED mana<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Meaning: If you are full mana and you are not casting SOMETHING on SOMEONE, you are wasting mana.<P>When you start out FM, and are standing there looking at your tank, you can wait and wait til he gets low enough to warrant a Complete Heal or a Greater Heal or whatever you have. OR you can throw a LOW aggro, Heal over Time on him, and SIT DOWN.<P>This provides your tank some buffer time to get solid aggro, heal him, and gives you a reason to sit. Often times, by the time the HoT wears off, you are back to FM and can throw another one on him. With judicial use of mana and sit time, you can be FM or nearly FM at the end of the fight and your puller can grab another MOB right away.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dynarik Ferox</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/agree Dikmer</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
